		these sections just show the jobs entered in the /etc/cron.d/backup file (for 'scheduled jobs'), a /var/log/backup/completed.log (which will have the job name & date/time stamp outputted to this file each time one
		is run), and finally the output from /var/log/issues.log (which will output issues redirected from the cron like "backup.sh ... >/var/log/backup.log 2>|tee ..."); see the following links:
			https://www.systutorials.com/241650/how-to-make-tee-catch-the-stderr-only-in-linux/
			https://stackoverflow.com/questions/692000/how-do-i-write-stderr-to-a-file-while-using-tee-with-a-pipe

			see the t.sh and w(rapper).sh files in this directory (taken from the two links above) for logging
			see the tarp.sh script that does all the logging, cataloging, error control, etc

		jobs(cheduler).sh	the script responsible for the scheduling via cron for the various saved jobs		NOTE: @cli level, all of these have configurable switches ONLY, no walk-throughs; of course there is this GUI also
		backup.sh		the script responsible for tar-based backups
		synchronize.sh		the script responsible for rsync/unison duplication
		restore.sh		the script responsible for restoring selected data from archives

		pre/post		scripts to execute locally before and after backup/sync job
		pre-mount/post-mount	scripts to execute (in location of SOURCE [e.g. ssh, sshfs = remote; cifs, nfs, local = local]) before and after backup/sync job	< this will enable us to mount server share in DPIES/NetBUD *before* executing the sync job (since that share is not mounted otherwise)

